sec.p:
Evidence suggesting 2 Cygni's binary nature consists of multiepoch, multiinstrument, multifilter direct imaging detection of a candidate source with relative brightness, colors, and spectrum consistent with companionship. The off-axis source can likely only be detected using AO (or possibly speckle imaging) on a large telescope. The false-positive probability of a nearby foreground or background stellar source located in such close proximity to 2 Cygni with these attributes is less than one in  23 × 106(



1/4.3×10-8

).
